1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson we will create and customize a header and footer.

2
00:00:04,860 --> 00:00:07,860
Block themes allow us to build our entire site using blocks,

3
00:00:08,860 --> 00:00:11,860
including pages, posts, templates and template parts.

4
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:15,700
We have already explored nesting blocks and using block patterns.

5
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:19,600
In this session, I'm going to create and customize the header and footer of my site

6
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:24,100
using patterns that come with my theme.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Header and footer patterns provide a strong foundation to work from

8
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:30,960
and most of the layout has already been done for you.

9
00:00:32,300 --> 00:00:35,300
Before we start, I wanted to highlight that I am using the Twenty Twenty-Four block theme

10
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:41,360
and if I go to Settings, Reading, you will notice I have set a static

11
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:46,860
home page and posts page.

12
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,360
And because I've done this, if we make our way to pages and open up our home page,

13
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,200
we will notice that our home page has been assigned to the default page template,

14
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:01,380
the same as the other pages in my navigation menu.

15
00:01:03,240 --> 00:01:06,240
Let's go ahead and get started.

16
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:09,280
We will make our way to the Site Editor, where we can edit and update our templates.

17
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:14,980
Please note, at this stage all of our templates share the same header and footer.

18
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,960
So if we open up our pages template, for example,

19
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,760
we will notice it is the same as our 404 template and single posts template, for example.

20
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:34,440
But what does that mean?

21
00:01:33,160 --> 00:01:36,160
It means if we customize the current header and footer template part, it will update

22
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,600
automatically on all the templates it's on.

23
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:43,640
But if I replace the header or footer on a template, I will need to manually replace

24
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:48,360
it on all the other templates I'm going to use it as well.

25
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,800
So, withou further ado I'm going to open up my page template and start customizing

26
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:56,960
my header and footer.

27
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:59,200
Let's start with the header and open up the List View.

28
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:04,200
I want to replace the header, so I'll click on the three vertical dots and then select

29
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:08,240
Replace header.

30
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:10,160
And now I can select from a range of patterns that come with my theme.

31
00:02:11,320 --> 00:02:14,320
I'm going to select Header inside full width background image.

32
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:19,640
Once selected, I'm going to start modifying.

33
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:23,440
I will make sure I select the Cover block and then replace the background image

34
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:29,760
with an image I've already uploaded to my media library.

35
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:34,080
Next, I will select the Site Logo block and upload a transparent image that I've saved

36
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:42,360
as a logo in my media library.

37
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:45,920
Then I will select the Cover block again, open Styles and change the opacity to zero

38
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:52,200
as I've selected a light image.

39
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:55,240
Once I've done that, I will select my Site Title block and choose a darker text color.

40
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:03,240
Then I will click on the three vertical dots next to Typography, select Font family and

41
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:09,200
choose a new font.

42
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:13,200
I also want to enlarge the site title so I will go ahead and set a custom size.

43
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:22,160
Then we can move on to our Navigation block.

44
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,840
Once the Navigation block is selected, I'll open Styles, change the color of the text,

45
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:33,520
change the font family and also enlarge my navigation menu

46
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:43,160
by setting a custom size.

47
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:48,840
The last step I want to take is to add some padding around my Row block.

48
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:52,440
So I'll open up my Styles and below dimensions, add some more padding to create some more

49
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:57,240
space around the text.

50
00:03:57,520 --> 00:04:00,520
And then our new header is done.

51
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,080
The next step of course is to save and then to update my other templates with this new

52
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:12,600
header that I've created using patterns.

53
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,320
So for example, let's go ahead and open up our 404 template and replace the header.

54
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:29,520
And now you will see it below Existing template parts.

55
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,440
We can save and then follow the same process for all the other relevant templates.

56
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:42,520
Now we can return to our page template and move on to our footer.

57
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:47,560
In this case, I'm not going to replace the footer, I am merely going to update the existing

58
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:53,320
pattern and then it will automatically update on all the other templates.

59
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:58,560
Firstly, I will enlarge the Site Logo block and then I will add my site tagline to the

60
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,840
Site Tagline block below the site title.

61
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:15,200
Now we can move on to the three columns on the right.

62
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,200
I will select the title of the middle block and change it to Quick links.

63
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:29,240
Then I will select the Navigation block which has been added with dummy content.

64
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:35,120
And in the sidebar settings next to menu, I'll click on the three vertical dots and select

65
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,600
the header navigation.

66
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,640
I will also open the settings tab and double check that the orientation is vertical.

67
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:50,600
Now we can move on to the next column and this time I'm going to replace the dummy content

68
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:58,160
with a new navigation menu.

69
00:05:57,560 --> 00:06:00,560
So I'll click on Create new menu and then select the privacy policy page which I have

70
00:06:06,960 --> 00:06:09,960
already created as well as the terms and conditions page.

71
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:21,320
And in the last column, I will make sure that I update the links to my social media platforms.

72
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:27,680
So at the moment, there's dummy content and therefore I will replace the hashtag with

73
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:32,760
the correct link.

74
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:35,320
And now my footer is done but I can of course make further modifications.

75
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:41,320
After saving, we can make our way to our other templates, for example the 404 template and

76
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,880
we will see that the footer updated automatically.

77
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
And here is a view on the front end when I visit my contact page.

78
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:03,560
I trust header and footer patterns will give you a boost and provide you a strong foundation

79
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:07,920
for your header and footer design.

